        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The hearth priestess calls upon her deity and connection with the hearth to enhance her allies. The priestess empowers one friendly creature she can see within 30 feet of her with one of the following options until the start of her next turn.<ul><li>Hearth’s Burn. The target’s weapon ignites, and when the target hits with the weapon, the weapon deals an extra 3 (1d6) fire damage.</li><li>Hearth’s Comfort. If the target is charmed or frightened, the condition immediately ends. In addition, the target gains 5 (1d10) temporary hp.</li><li>Hearth’s Protection. The target’s Armor Class increases by 2, and its armor is immune to spells and effects that target or affect the armor, such as the heat metal spell or a rust monster’s antennae.</li>",
          "source": {
            "book": "",
            "fallback": "",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
